  "decision_notes": "The problem is a prefix-free code optimization problem. To ensure no ID is a prefix of another, we need to extend the strings such that they form a prefix-free set. This is equivalent to ensuring that in a Trie of the final strings, no leaf is an ancestor of another leaf. The cost is the sum of added bits. This can be modeled by analyzing the Trie structure of the original IDs and determining how many bits must be added to each path to resolve prefix conflicts.",
