    },
    {
      "label": "greedy_optimization_logic",
      "instructions": "Formulate a greedy strategy to minimize the total bits added. Given the Trie structure, if a node is marked as an end-of-string, any path passing through it must be extended. If multiple strings share a prefix, calculate the minimum extensions required to make them unique and prefix-free. This is related to the concept of a prefix-free code where we want to minimize the sum of (length_after - length_before)."
    }
  ],
  "synthesis_brief": "Combine the Trie structure analysis with the greedy optimization strategy. The final solution should involve building a Trie, identifying prefix conflicts, and calculating the minimum bits to add to each string to ensure that no string is a prefix of another, which can be solved by traversing the Trie and counting necessary extensions at conflict nodes."
}

